text: Stelpurnar okkar (English: Our girls) is an Icelandic documentary film about the Icelandic women's national football team's quest to be the first Icelandic national football team to advance to a major continental tournament. It was directed by Þóra Tómasdóttir and produced by Krumma Films and premiered in Háskólabíó on 14 August 2009. The documentary was filmed during the team's games in the UEFA Women's Euro 2009 qualifying. ==References== ==External links== * *Official site Category:2009 documentary films Category:Icelandic documentary films Category:Icelandic films Category:Documentary films about association football
